1773177395740354	1	itc:v3:AWKTMnkmSTJyZnQAAAAAQa2vVqtdbcAAAAEyFw		item.create	bn-2uho	{"description":"Edict still emits pre-v0.53 maw guidance in multiple places, especially bare `maw ws create --random` workspace creation and implicit-target merge flows. Audit and update every generated doc/template/runtime command builder so Edict matches current maw behavior and can safely drive modern target-aware workflows.\n\nBreaking changes to absorb:\n- `maw ws create` now requires an explicit source: use `--from main` for trunk work or `--change <change-id>` for change-bound work. Old `maw ws create --random` guidance is now broken.\n- Non-interactive merges must provide `--message`; remove any remaining merge examples/tests that rely on old implicit messaging behavior.\n- Repo/workspace deterministic simulation ergonomics should not point at `maw dev sim`; if Edict references simulation helpers, use repo-local `just`/script workflows, and reserve `bn dev sim` for bones protocol simulation only.\n\nFeature/contract changes to adopt:\n- Prefer explicit `--into default` in generated merge guidance so target-aware maw flows are unambiguous and change-target merges can swap targets cleanly.\n- Add first-class support for `maw ws create --change <id>` and `maw ws merge --into <change-id>` anywhere Edict coordinates tracked changes.\n- Revalidate all maw-parsing code and guidance against current JSON/exit contracts (`merge --check`, `ws conflicts --format json`, `ws history --format json` annotation payloads, `ws sync --all` incomplete semantics).\n\nAcceptance criteria:\n- Audit AGENTS/docs/templates/protocol renderers/executors/tests and any generated shell guidance in Edict.\n- Replace broken create guidance with explicit source-aware commands.\n- Update change-tracking workflows to use new maw flags/features where appropriate.\n- Verify runtime command parsing/tests match current maw output and exit semantics.\n- Regenerate synced docs/templates so initialized projects inherit the new maw usage.","kind":"task","title":"Switch Edict to maw post-v0.53 flags and target-aware workflows"}	blake3:fY3klDtxcEs6A5CndzOlJU5y4wWCIprSrh1cJZlZyd0
1773177395777248	1	itc:v3:AWKTMnkmSTJyZnQAAAAAQa2vVqtdbcAAAAEyGA		item.comment	bn-2uho	{"body":"Concrete hotspots already visible from grep in Edict:\n- `AGENTS.md` still documents `maw ws create <name> [--random]`, `maw ws create --random`, and merge examples without explicit `--into default`.\n- Workflow docs with broken create guidance: `.agents/edict/start.md`, `.agents/edict/worker-loop.md`, `start.md`, `worker-loop.md`, `src/templates/docs/start.md`, `src/templates/docs/worker-loop.md`, `src/templates/docs/mission.md`.\n- Protocol/runtime command builders that likely need updates: `src/commands/protocol/shell.rs`, `src/commands/protocol/render.rs`, `src/commands/protocol/executor.rs`, `src/commands/protocol/merge.rs`, `src/commands/protocol/finish.rs`, `src/commands/protocol/resume.rs`, `src/commands/dev_loop/prompt.rs`.\n- Additional docs likely needing target-aware merge wording: `.agents/edict/finish.md`, `.agents/edict/merge-check.md`, `docs/dev-agent-architecture.md`, generated template copies under `src/templates/docs/`.\n\nSuggested implementation plan:\n1. Introduce one canonical helper/renderer for source-aware workspace creation (`--from main` vs `--change <id>`), then fan it through protocol text/tests.\n2. Make lead/worker merge instructions explicit about `--into default` unless a tracked change target is active.\n3. Audit any Edict code that parses maw stdout/stderr/JSON and pin tests to the post-v0.53 contracts.\n4. Re-sync generated docs/templates and confirm a freshly initialized project gets only modern maw commands."}	blake3:uMHEUZE7GQJRRXdc4WF7riaQi_pNfciCv0lIzrAU-Ug
1773348675307204	1	itc:v3:AWKTMnkmSTJyZnQAAAAAQa2vVqtdbcAAAAEyGQ		item.move	bn-2uho	{"state":"doing"}	blake3:nJDhaCSLiKKkKg7tJ6iPNWvvXJP1nsopX7jFypl5Jes
